          <h1>Toast messages</h1>
          <div class="breakout">
            <p>Toast messages provide simple feedback about an operation in a small popup.</p>
          </div>

          <h2>Purpose</h2>
          <p>Toast messages are ideal for situations when you just want to give the user a heads-up. They are a great way for you
            to confirm that that thing the user was doing really did happen.</p>

          <p>Toast messages
            <strong>do not</strong> require a user response. If user response to a status message is required, consider instead using
            a
            <a href="/styleguide/modals">modal</a> or a
            <a href="/styleguide/notifications">notification</a>.
          </p>
          <p>Here is an example of a toast message being triggered by a button</p>
          <button class="uikit-btn call-toast" role="alert" type="button">Trigger Toast Success</button>

